    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Interior Rear View Mirror</title>
        <para>The interior rear view mirror is located directly above the driver position. The mirror is mounted on two
            brackets attached to the windshield header assembly.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the mounting screws on the mirror bracket assembly attaching the brackets to the
                header assembly. Loosen and remove the screws on each bracket.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the mirror assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f47006205" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g47006205.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 205. Driver Interior Rear View Mirror</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. DRIVER INTERIOR REAR VIEW MIRROR</callout1>
                <callout1>2. REAR VIEW MIRROR MOUNTING BRACKETS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. FRONT INTERIOR HEADER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>4. SUN VISOR ASSEMBLY</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove the mirror glass, remove the nuts and bolts on the mirror to release the adapter
                bracket.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the adapter bracket, rubber strip and the metal backing plate.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the mirror glass and discard (if mirror glass is broken or cracked).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The inside rear view mirror should be carefully inspected for small chips. If chips are
                found, do not install.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
